      "label": "mathematical_formalism_specialist",
      "instructions": "Establish the formal mathematical relationship between the redundancy measures used in Quantum Darwinism (such as the mutual information between the system and fragments of the environment) and the code properties of Holographic Quantum Error Correction (such as the recovery of bulk operators from boundary subregions). Detail how the concept of 'information redundancy' in QD translates to the 'error-correcting' properties of the holographic code."
    },
    {
      "label": "literature_gap_analyst",
      "instructions": "Conduct a targeted review of current theoretical physics literature to identify if a formal, unified mathematical framework currently exists that bridges QD and HQEC. Specifically, look for 'citation gaps' where researchers have proposed intuitive similarities but have failed to provide a rigorous, unified proof or a single overarching model that encompasses both phenomena."
    }
